Here's the ViewModel using **CommunityToolkit.Mvvm** (recommended) plus a XAML page with compiled bindings:

**ViewModel — `ProductDetailViewModel.cs`**

```csharp
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.ComponentModel;
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.Input;

namespace MyApp.ViewModels;

public partial class ProductDetailViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string _name = string.Empty;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private decimal _price;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _isAvailable;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _isBusy;

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task LoadAsync()
    {
        if (IsBusy) return;

        try
        {
            IsBusy = true;

            // Replace with your actual data service call
            await Task.Delay(500);

            Name = "Wireless Headphones";
            Price = 79.99m;
            IsAvailable = true;
        }
        finally
        {
            IsBusy = false;
        }
    }
}
```

The source generator creates public properties (`Name`, `Price`, `IsAvailable`, `IsBusy`) with `PropertyChanged` notifications, and a `LoadCommand` from `LoadAsync`.

**XAML Page — `ProductDetailPage.xaml`**

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:MyApp.ViewModels"
             x:Class="MyApp.Views.ProductDetailPage"
             x:DataType="vm:ProductDetailViewModel"
             Title="Product Detail">

    <VerticalStackLayout Padding="20" Spacing="12">
        <Label Text="{Binding Name}"
               FontSize="24" FontAttributes="Bold" />

        <Label Text="{Binding Price, StringFormat='Price: {0:C2}'}" />

        <Label Text="{Binding IsAvailable, StringFormat='In Stock: {0}'}" />

        <ActivityIndicator IsRunning="{Binding IsBusy}"
                           IsVisible="{Binding IsBusy}" />

        <Button Text="Load Product"
                Command="{Binding LoadCommand}" />
    </VerticalStackLayout>
</ContentPage>
```

**Code-behind — `ProductDetailPage.xaml.cs`**

```csharp
namespace MyApp.Views;

public partial class ProductDetailPage : ContentPage
{
    public ProductDetailPage(ProductDetailViewModel vm)
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        BindingContext = vm;
    }
}
```

**Key points:**

- `[ObservableProperty]` generates the public property + `PropertyChanged` raise — no boilerplate.
- `[RelayCommand]` generates `LoadCommand` (an `IAsyncRelayCommand`) that disables itself while running.
- `x:DataType` at the page root enables **compiled bindings** (8–20× faster, AOT-safe).
- Add `<WarningsAsErrors>XC0022;XC0025</WarningsAsErrors>` to your `.csproj` to catch binding mistakes at build time.

**NuGet requirement:** `CommunityToolkit.Mvvm` (≥ 8.0).
